  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Frontend App**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focused on the frontend application\'s architecture. I\'m planning to build a single-screen app with Next.js, React, and Tailwind CSS. The design should be formal. I\'m currently thinking through how to implement the \"Snowflakes\" and \"Balloons\" button functionality, specifically the snowflake animation, which should be medium-sized.\n\n\n**Planning Animation Execution**\n\nI\'ve outlined the execution plan for the snowflake and balloon animations. First, I\'ll update `metadata.json` and create `app/page.tsx`. Next, I will use `motion/react` (formerly framer-motion) for the animations, creating distinct `Snowflake` and `Balloon` components. The app will be designed to run for a duration of 5 seconds for each animation. I might need to manage the animation states for controlling their timing and visibility.\n\n\n**Refining UI Component Choices**\n\nI\'m now reconsidering my UI component choices. Initially, I thought emojis would be fine for the snowflake and balloon icons, but for a \"formal\" design, I need something more refined. I\'ve re-checked Lucide and found a suitable Snowflake, but I\'ll have to create a simple SVG for the balloon. It will likely need to be a simple SVG to avoid looking silly.\nI\'m also working on designing the layout to accommodate those.\n\n\n**Defining Aesthetic Guidelines**\n\nI\'m now establishing the formal design principles: muted colors, elegant typography, and a structured layout. I\'m thinking background will be a slate or gray, with dark text. I\'ll use Inter as the font unless a user explicitly requests something like Playfair Display. The main file to focus on is app/page.tsx, so I\'m writing this.\n\n\n**Implementing the Button Design**\n\nI\'m now implementing the UI elements. I\'ve written the HTML for the buttons, using a `div` for layout, and `button` elements for each button, and I\'m updating the `className` properties on those. I\'m focusing on the \"Celebration Controls\" section. This uses Tailwind CSS for styling, and I\'m focusing on disabled states and hover effects for interactivity. The goal is a clean, modern look.\n\n\n**Refining Animation Components**\n\nI\'m now integrating the animation components, focusing on the containers for snowflakes and balloons. I\'ve updated the `app/page.tsx` file to incorporate `SnowflakeContainer` and `BalloonContainer`. I\'m using state to toggle the visibility of each, controlling animation playback. The `SnowflakeContainer` uses `AnimatePresence` for smooth entrance and exit animations. Inside the `SnowflakeContainer`, I\'m creating random particle positions and durations for dynamic visuals.\n\n\n**Developing Animation Parameters**\n\nI\'ve been working on the animation parameters for the snowflakes and balloons. For the snowflakes, I\'m defining initial positions, opacity, and rotation, and then animating them to move downwards with variable duration and a slight sway. For the balloons, I\'m setting random positions and durations upon component mount, ensuring a unique and dynamic display.\n\n\n**Finalizing Particle Animations**\n\nI\'m now completing the particle animations, making sure they look just right. For snowflakes, I\'m defining initial conditions for position, opacity, and rotation, and then animating them to float down with varying speeds and subtle sway. For balloons, I\'m setting their position and how long they\'ll last on the screen randomly when they get loaded, to create a sense of randomness in the display.\n\n\n**Revising Balloon Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now revising the aesthetics of the balloon SVG for the formal application, and I\'ve updated the code for a more refined appearance. I\'ve considered muted colors, such as silver, gold, and navy blue, which fit better into a formal event. I\'m focusing on the `app/page.tsx` file for the updates.\n\n\n**Adjusting Balloon Colors**\n\nI\'m now implementing color adjustments, ensuring the formal application\'s elegance. I\'m focusing on the balloon and snowflake colors, ensuring they align with the design\'s muted palette. I\'ve considered randomizing Tailwind classes for the balloons or sticking to one color for a cohesive look. The snowflakes will be text-blue-100 or text-slate-300. I am also making sure the size of each is medium, with the snowflake at size 32, and the balloons at 40x60, and I am rethinking the five-second interval. It may require particle generation that lasts 5 seconds.\n\n\n**Optimizing Animation Duration**\n\nI\'m now refining the animation duration logic to align perfectly with the 5-second window. My current plan is to use `setTimeout` to control the container\'s visibility. I will ensure that the snowflakes and balloons are continuously generated within the active window. I\'m focusing on their generation, with delays and durations to ensure they all get their chance to appear, and disappear at the right time.\n\n\n**Refining Particle Generation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on particle generation, thinking through how to create a continuous animation within the 5-second window. I\'m considering rendering a container for the 5-second duration, and then giving the particles CSS animation `fall`, that takes 5 seconds, starting slightly above the viewport and ending slightly below. I can use negative animation delays for distribution. If I generate particles with delays ranging from 0 to 4 seconds, and speeds that allow them to fall in maybe 2-3 seconds, this could work. I can also have a lot of them.\n\n\n**Clarifying Event Duration**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the event duration. It seems the requirement means the entire falling action continues for 5 seconds. I\'ve realized if particles spawn with a 5-second delay and a 5-second duration, the whole sequence takes 10 seconds. I\'m going to have the particles fall for 5, and the container unmounts after 8 seconds to allow transitions to complete. I\'m going to rethink the calculation to align with the 5-second \"active\" time.\n\n\n**Refining Duration Implementation**\n\nI\'m now implementing the duration logic based on the user\'s specification. I need to ensure the animation of snowflakes and balloons runs consistently for 5 seconds. I\'m focusing on how I can properly calculate and coordinate the spawn of the various particles, and ensure the active animations run at the right time. I\'ll need to update the `app/page.tsx` file for the updates.\n\n\n\n**Implementing Event Duration**\n\nI\'m now implementing the event duration. After evaluating alternatives, I\'m focusing on handling particle generation and animation within the specified 5-second interval. I\'m focusing on the `app/page.tsx` file for the updates, particularly on the animation loop and the start and end of the animations. I need to make sure the animation looks just right.\n\n\n**Refining Function Implementation**\n\nI\'m now refining the functions to trigger and manage the snowflakes and balloons. I\'m focusing on the `handleBalloons` function, and how it is used with the existing functions. My current plan involves integrating them seamlessly with the UI, ensuring smooth transitions and managing state updates properly. I\'ll focus on the `setIsBallooning` and `setIsSnowing` to control the animation states and ensure that multiple events can not occur at the same time.\n\n\n\n**Integrating Event Management**\n\nI\'m now integrating the event management functions into the UI. I\'m focusing on the `handleSnowflakes` function with its impact on the event\'s duration, ensuring that it works alongside the current functionality for balloons. The plan is to trigger the snow and balloon events seamlessly. I am still using the `setIsSnowing` to control the animation states so that multiple events can not occur at the same time.\n\n\\n\\n\nOkay, I\'m now integrating the event management functions into the UI. I\'ve focused on integrating the `handleSnowflakes` function with the existing functionality for balloons, while ensuring the event runs for five seconds. I\'m leveraging `setIsSnowing` and `setIsBallooning` to control animation state transitions and prevent overlaps. The plan is to make the event seamless.\n\n\n**Adjusting Particle Timings**\n\nI\'m now implementing the particle timings to enhance the animation, ensuring a uniform distribution. I\'ve updated the particle generation logic to delay spawning up to 4 seconds, so they finish between 5-7 seconds. The animation duration now varies between 3 to 5 seconds with a slight sway, all in an attempt to be seamless.\n\n\n**Refining Particle Implementation**\n\nI\'m now refining the particle implementation with both snowflakes and balloons now implemented and generating particles appropriately. I have implemented a system where balloons spawn over 3 seconds and take 4-6 to rise with a slight sway. I have also made snowflakes generate randomly and fall at random rates. The plan is to create a seamless user experience.\n\n\n**Finalizing Balloon Logic**\n\nI\'m now completing the balloon logic within the codebase. I\'ve ensured seamless operation with the snowflakes, maintaining proper timing and visual appeal. I\'m focusing on the `handleBalloons` function to make sure that the animations start on time and look as good as possible, and I\'m updating `app/page.tsx` for integration.\n\n\n"
